    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I strongly advise against taking a high dose of ibuprofen without medical guidance. While 1200mg is above the recommended maximum dose for most adults, it may be more than the body can process safely. Taking too much ibuprofen can lead to severe side effects like stomach ulcers, bleeding, or kidney damage, especially if you have pre-existing conditions. The risks far outweigh any temporary relief from a stomach ache, and it's better to err on the side of caution and consult with a doctor or wait until morning to reassess your symptoms.",
      "source": "target",
